1.sudo apt-get install exuberant-ctags 
for c tage installation follow http://benoithamelin.tumblr.com/post/15101202004/using-vim-exuberant-ctags-easy-source-navigation
2.git clone https://github.com/rmk135/vimrc.git` #use setup.sh to install
#after installing the aboveadd the following to vimrc
3.open vi /tmp/a.py and install
:PluginInstall andviro/flake8-vim
then again add the following in vimrc
4.let mapleader=","
5.let python_highlight_all=1
6.let g:PyFlakeOnWrite = 1
7.se ic
8.nmap <leader>n :NERDTree
9.comment hte following in vimrc file, "autocmd BufWinLeave *.py :TagbarClose
10.nmap <leader>. :wq<CR>
Note : folding hte code and opening it is => za and double quotes opens the nerd tree windows "
#f9 ,f10 to navigate between opened files in tab
andviro/flake8-vim is installed from https://github.com/andviro/flake8-vim ,for more settings use https://github.com/andviro/flake8-vim docs
#git clone https://github.com/gmarik/Vundle.vim.git ~/.vim/bundle/Vundle.vim
